main event: On 17th May 1955 at 0818/041152, grapefruit-sized objects were observed for approximately 5 minutes over Mojave, California, causing interference with a TV set. One object flared, and the remaining two disappeared.
interesting points: The objects were described as round and bright, moving rapidly across the sky before disappearing at great speed.
The sighting caused TV sets to experience voice and picture interference.
A total of nine objects were observed, each approximately the size of a half dollar.
Six of the objects faded out, one flared, and the remaining two disappeared.
The report acknowledged the delay in receiving the preliminary report and the impossibility of further investigation, leading to the conclusion of 'possibly aircraft lights.'
